WEBVTT

00:03.873 --> 00:06.310
- Dr. Ben Song
risked everything

00:06.354 --> 00:08.747
when he used
the quantum leap accelerator

00:08.791 --> 00:10.488
to travel back in time.

00:10.532 --> 00:13.013
Now, our team's working
to find out why.

00:13.056 --> 00:17.234
As he leaps between bodies
with no memory of who he is,

00:17.278 --> 00:19.323
he still has one hope:

00:19.367 --> 00:23.632
that his next leap
takes him back

00:23.675 --> 00:29.029
to the place
and people he calls home.

00:30.117 --> 00:31.640
[plane engine roars]

00:31.683 --> 00:34.643
[dramatic music]

00:34.686 --> 00:35.992
♪

00:36.036 --> 00:37.211
[bell rings]

00:37.733 --> 00:41.215
[high-pitched ringing]
- Keep your hands up!

00:41.258 --> 00:42.303
[words echoing]
Why are you looking at me?

00:42.346 --> 00:44.174
He's the one
to keep your eyes on.

00:44.218 --> 00:45.349
- What just happened?

00:45.393 --> 00:46.785
There must be
a misunderstanding, okay?

00:46.829 --> 00:49.049
I--
[ears ringing]

00:49.092 --> 00:51.790
[suspenseful music]

00:51.834 --> 00:52.965
♪

00:53.009 --> 00:54.228
- I did four combinations
like you said.

00:54.271 --> 00:55.838
- You good, you good.

00:55.881 --> 00:59.711
Little brother here just
got distracted is all.

00:59.755 --> 01:03.063
Danny, you straight?

01:03.106 --> 01:04.673
You know where you are?

01:04.716 --> 01:06.066
- Not really.

01:06.109 --> 01:07.893
- Psh.

01:07.937 --> 01:10.070
Go ahead, hit the showers.

01:10.113 --> 01:13.899
♪

01:13.943 --> 01:16.032
- Coach, I'm sorry.

01:16.076 --> 01:18.121
- It's all good.

01:18.165 --> 01:21.081
[soft dramatic music]

01:21.124 --> 01:27.609
♪

01:27.652 --> 01:30.046
- [grunting]
- There we go.

01:30.090 --> 01:34.268
♪

01:37.009 --> 01:41.013
♪

01:41.057 --> 01:43.755
- [grunts]
I am jacked.

01:43.799 --> 01:45.148
♪

01:45.192 --> 01:48.238
[grunts]

01:48.282 --> 01:50.458
- Uh,
am I disturbing you two, or...

01:50.501 --> 01:51.633
I can come back if you want.

01:51.676 --> 01:53.069
It's a perk
of being a hologram.

01:53.113 --> 01:56.203
Just--
- Addison, what went wrong?

01:56.246 --> 01:57.900
This makes three leaps now.
You said I'd be--

01:57.943 --> 01:59.162
- Look, we are still trying

01:59.206 --> 02:00.642
to make sense of the code
that you uploaded.

02:00.685 --> 02:03.645
So until then,
I say that you and I

02:03.688 --> 02:06.517
focus on getting you safely
through whatever this leap is.

02:06.561 --> 02:08.780
- [sighs]

02:08.824 --> 02:09.825
♪

02:09.868 --> 02:12.828
All right.
[electronic chiming]

02:12.871 --> 02:14.438
Okay, your name is--

02:14.482 --> 02:18.094
- Danny Hill.
I'm a boxer in Las Vegas.

02:18.138 --> 02:20.836
We're in the 1970s.

02:20.879 --> 02:22.446
- Look at you,
getting the hang of this.

02:22.490 --> 02:25.623
You are indeed Danny Hill,
we are in Vegas,

02:25.667 --> 02:28.626
and the date
is October 2, 1977.

02:28.670 --> 02:31.455
Groove three.
- Did you say October 2, 1977?

02:31.499 --> 02:32.891
- Yeah.
Why?

02:32.935 --> 02:35.285
- God, someone up there
does not like me.

02:35.329 --> 02:37.940
I've just leapt into
the body of a fighter

02:37.983 --> 02:39.246
whose title shot is tomorrow.

02:39.289 --> 02:40.812
- What?
- Yeah.

02:40.856 --> 02:43.598
- Okay.
[negative electronic chimes]

02:43.641 --> 02:45.382
Sorry, Ziggy's running slow.

02:45.426 --> 02:48.603
Okay, uh--ah.

02:48.646 --> 02:49.995
- Ah?

02:50.039 --> 02:51.127
He lost, didn't he?

02:51.171 --> 02:53.521
- Yeah, evidently.

02:53.564 --> 02:55.218
I mean,
Danny was the odds-on favorite,

02:55.262 --> 02:56.741
but something went wrong.

02:56.785 --> 02:58.874
Newspaper reports
that he fought sloppy

02:58.917 --> 03:00.484
like he was distracted.

03:00.528 --> 03:01.833
He got knocked out
in the second round,

03:01.877 --> 03:03.531
and his career
never really recovered.

03:03.574 --> 03:05.489
- It's hard to believe
I'd leap into someone

03:05.533 --> 03:07.056
to help them win a fight.

03:07.099 --> 03:08.753
♪

03:08.797 --> 03:10.581
- Maybe you're here
to find the distraction.

03:10.625 --> 03:12.235
[door latch clicks]
[approaching footsteps]

03:12.279 --> 03:18.415
♪

03:18.459 --> 03:20.025
Mystery solved.

03:20.069 --> 03:22.854
♪

03:22.898 --> 03:24.943
- Hey, you.

03:24.987 --> 03:27.381
- Uh, I'm not getting anything
on her, Ben.

03:27.424 --> 03:28.773
- I know I'm not supposed
to be here,

03:28.817 --> 03:31.733
but I wanted to give you these
for luck.

03:33.213 --> 03:35.737
- Shoelaces.
- [laughs]

03:35.780 --> 03:37.521
Shoelaces.
You're funny.

03:37.565 --> 03:40.089
- They're for your gloves,
lover boy.

03:40.132 --> 03:42.526
- Now when you step
into the ring tomorrow night,

03:42.570 --> 03:46.095
I will be with you
because I am with you

03:46.138 --> 03:48.663
even though I can't be
by your side just yet, okay?

03:48.706 --> 03:51.709
- Danny,
what's taking so long--

03:51.753 --> 03:53.363
you shouldn't be here, Angela.

03:53.407 --> 03:54.582
- It's only for a minute.

03:54.625 --> 03:56.540
- You know,
you say you love my brother,

03:56.584 --> 03:58.325
you say you want
what's best for him,

03:58.368 --> 03:59.761
but if that's true,
you leave right now.

03:59.804 --> 04:01.023
- Hey.

04:01.066 --> 04:02.154
- And not do anything else
to distract him

04:02.198 --> 04:04.809
before the biggest fight
of his life.

04:04.853 --> 04:06.594
That's what someone
who loves him would do.

04:06.637 --> 04:08.944
- Then that's what I'll do.

04:08.987 --> 04:11.947
♪

04:11.990 --> 04:13.949
[sighs]

04:13.992 --> 04:15.559
♪

04:15.603 --> 04:17.126
- Was that necessary?

04:17.169 --> 04:18.562
- Funny coming from the guy

04:18.606 --> 04:21.261
who just got his ass kicked
by his sparring partner.

04:21.304 --> 04:22.523
Weigh in is in an hour.

04:22.566 --> 04:24.481
Hurry up.
Get dressed.

04:24.525 --> 04:31.706
♪

04:31.749 --> 04:33.273
- [chuckles]

04:33.316 --> 04:35.449
I always wanted a brother.

04:35.492 --> 04:37.973
♪

04:38.016 --> 04:40.715
But I'm an only child.

04:40.758 --> 04:43.500
- Yeah, that's right, Ben.

04:43.544 --> 04:45.937
Do you remember anything else?

04:45.981 --> 04:48.940
♪

04:48.984 --> 04:51.073
Okay.

04:51.116 --> 04:53.771
[Marvin Gaye's
"Got to Give It Up"]

04:53.815 --> 04:56.644
- ♪ I used to go out
to parties ♪

04:56.687 --> 04:59.168
- Okay, Daryl "The Hammer" Hill
is Danny's only family.

04:59.211 --> 05:01.475
Their parents died in a fire
when Danny was just eight.

05:01.518 --> 05:03.346
- So Daryl raised Danny
and protected him.

05:03.390 --> 05:04.478
- Yeah,
and taught him how to fight.

05:04.521 --> 05:06.001
Daryl was a top-ranked boxer
himself

05:06.044 --> 05:08.264
before he got drafted
into Vietnam.

05:08.308 --> 05:09.787
Never fought after that.

05:09.831 --> 05:11.528
- So Danny's getting me
the title shot Daryl never had.

05:11.572 --> 05:15.706
- He's married, wife Penny,
no kids though.

05:15.750 --> 05:17.186
I can't see anything
else significant.

05:17.229 --> 05:18.318
- Are you nervous?

05:18.361 --> 05:19.710
- Actually, yeah.

05:19.754 --> 05:22.060
- Now you just remember...

05:22.104 --> 05:25.803
you're Danny Hill,
best damn fighter in the world.

05:25.847 --> 05:28.458
And you will be champion
tomorrow.

05:28.502 --> 05:30.721
I've seen it.

05:30.765 --> 05:31.809
Let's go.

05:31.853 --> 05:34.377
- ♪ Keep on dancin'

05:34.421 --> 05:38.294
♪ [vocalizing]

05:38.338 --> 05:39.730
♪ Keep on dancin'

05:39.774 --> 05:42.429
- Ladies and gentlemen,
first up on the scale,

05:42.472 --> 05:44.692
hailing from Youngstown, Ohio,

05:44.735 --> 05:48.739
with a professional record
of 37 wins and no losses,

05:48.783 --> 05:51.960
23 of those wins by knockout,

05:52.003 --> 05:53.570
ladies and gentlemen,
the middleweight champion

05:53.614 --> 05:57.444
of the world, Roy Gordon!

05:57.487 --> 06:00.664
[cheers and applause]

06:00.708 --> 06:03.493
[flash bulbs popping]

06:03.537 --> 06:06.191
- I hate the damn cameras.

06:06.235 --> 06:08.498
[flash bulbs popping]

06:08.542 --> 06:14.025
- 160 pounds!
[cheers and applause]

06:14.069 --> 06:16.593
- I'm not going to lie, Ben.
He looks pretty mad.

06:16.637 --> 06:17.812
He looks like he wants
to kill you.

06:17.855 --> 06:19.379
- Not helping.
- Sorry.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.076
- And our challenger,

06:21.119 --> 06:24.645
born and raised right here
in Las Vegas,

06:24.688 --> 06:28.126
trained by local legend
Daryl "The Hammer" Hill

06:28.170 --> 06:31.652
with a perfect record
of 14 wins, no losses,

06:31.695 --> 06:35.525
all 14 of those wins
by knockout,

06:35.569 --> 06:40.225
ladies and gentlemen,
Danny Youngblood Hill!

06:40.269 --> 06:43.533
[cheers and applause]

06:43.577 --> 06:47.232
161 pounds!

06:47.276 --> 06:49.713
[upbeat music]

06:49.757 --> 06:52.629
- Well, at least we know
why Danny's been distracted.

06:52.673 --> 06:54.718
- ♪ I'm a starchild

06:54.762 --> 06:58.635
♪ No, no, I said a starchild

06:58.679 --> 07:01.943
- You're in love
with the champ's girlfriend.

07:01.986 --> 07:04.685
- ♪ Mm, I said a starchild

07:04.728 --> 07:07.296
[upbeat rock music]

07:07.339 --> 07:08.602
♪

07:08.645 --> 07:11.561
[mysterious dramatic music]

07:11.605 --> 07:14.129
♪

07:14.172 --> 07:16.958
- Ian, I have 24 hours
to teach Ben how to box.

07:17.001 --> 07:18.307
And not just box,

07:18.350 --> 07:19.961
defeat the middleweight
champion of the world.

07:20.004 --> 07:21.266
- Yeah, it's--

07:21.310 --> 07:22.790
- I need the footage
from the original bout,

07:22.833 --> 07:23.834
all the stats on Roy Gordon.
- Addison, Addison, Addison--

07:23.878 --> 07:25.270
- I need every fight
he ever did.

07:25.314 --> 07:26.446
I'm looking for weaknesses.
I'm looking for issues--

07:26.489 --> 07:27.621
- Hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey--

07:27.664 --> 07:29.231
- I'm looking--
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

07:29.274 --> 07:30.928
Look, I know, I know.

07:30.972 --> 07:32.974
I'm gonna get you
everything you need.

07:33.017 --> 07:34.454
You know that.

07:34.497 --> 07:35.585
- Thanks.

07:35.629 --> 07:37.761
Sorry, I didn't mean
to roll over you.

07:37.805 --> 07:40.982
- Look, I know this is gonna
be a very stupid question...

07:41.025 --> 07:44.115
[chuckling]
But are you okay?

07:44.159 --> 07:45.595
- Of course not.

07:45.639 --> 07:48.511
- I mean, we don't know
how long this is gonna last.

07:48.555 --> 07:50.426
I've been going over the code

07:50.470 --> 07:53.777
that Ben uploaded
just before he left.

07:53.821 --> 07:57.781
Addison, he might be
stuck out there a while.

07:57.825 --> 07:59.957
Look, you've been
burning it at both ends,

08:00.001 --> 08:01.785
and it's gonna catch up
with you if you don't

08:01.829 --> 08:03.047
take better care of yourself.

08:03.091 --> 08:04.179
- I'm taking care of myself.
- Really, Gabby?

08:04.222 --> 08:05.746
When was the last time
that you slept

08:05.789 --> 08:07.965
or ate something that
wasn't from a vending machine?

08:08.009 --> 08:09.793
- But look, I can't just stop.

08:09.837 --> 08:13.536
Okay, everything here
reminds me of him.

08:13.580 --> 08:15.625
Everything at home
reminds me of him.

08:15.669 --> 08:18.149
Even the day of the week
reminds me of him.

08:18.193 --> 08:22.284
- [chuckles]
So, like, Wednesday?

08:22.327 --> 08:24.591
Wednesday reminds you of Ben?

08:24.634 --> 08:26.288
- On Wednesdays,
we used to get Thai food

08:26.331 --> 08:31.162
and watch "Real Housewives
of Beverly Hills."

08:31.206 --> 08:32.120
- Wow.

08:32.163 --> 08:33.251
- He pretends like he hates it,

08:33.295 --> 08:35.471
but he follows all of them
on Twitter.

08:35.515 --> 08:39.040
- No, no.
- Yeah. [chuckles]

08:39.083 --> 08:41.564
- But...

08:41.608 --> 08:44.654
but he doesn't
remember that now.

08:44.698 --> 08:47.222
He doesn't remember
why he did this.

08:47.265 --> 08:50.486
And he doesn't even
remember me, so...

08:50.530 --> 08:55.883
yeah, it's been kind of hard
to eat and sleep or think.

08:55.926 --> 08:59.408
So, yeah, I might not be
taking the best care of myself,

08:59.451 --> 09:01.758
but doing the best I can.

09:01.802 --> 09:05.022
[soft dramatic music]

09:05.066 --> 09:07.634
♪

09:07.677 --> 09:10.506
- We're gonna get through this.

09:10.550 --> 09:12.552
Okay?

09:12.595 --> 09:14.031
- Hey.
- Thanks.

09:14.075 --> 09:16.468
- Magic wants us in his office.

09:16.512 --> 09:18.427
- Okay.
[sighs]

09:18.470 --> 09:20.342
- I had another call
from the Pentagon.

09:20.385 --> 09:22.039
They know our power draw is up.

09:22.083 --> 09:24.172
They know something
is going on.

09:24.215 --> 09:25.260
I can put them off.

09:25.303 --> 09:26.653
I just need to know
if I'm coming up

09:26.696 --> 09:29.133
with a short-term lie
or something longer.

09:29.177 --> 09:31.092
- Well, I finished going
through all the new code

09:31.135 --> 09:35.183
that Ben uploaded just before
he leapt, and we were right.

09:35.226 --> 09:38.055
Ben is trying to get to a
specific moment in space-time.

09:38.099 --> 09:39.709
- We just can't tell
where or when.

09:39.753 --> 09:41.406
- If we take
the first moment that he left

09:41.450 --> 09:42.756
and we use it as a center,

09:42.799 --> 09:45.585
then I think that each leap
is a stopping point

09:45.628 --> 09:47.412
on a way to this endpoint.

09:47.456 --> 09:49.240
What's not clear is the path
he's taking to get there.

09:49.284 --> 09:51.068
- Why not?

09:51.112 --> 09:52.548
- Well, for starters,
Ben just leapt into a past

09:52.592 --> 09:54.898
that's beyond his own lifetime.

09:54.942 --> 09:57.597
- That's supposed
to be impossible.

09:57.640 --> 09:59.076
- Yeah, it was,

09:59.120 --> 10:01.644
but Ben got rid of almost all
of our safety protocols

10:01.688 --> 10:05.126
before he got into the machine,
so nothing's impossible now.

10:05.169 --> 10:07.650
- How many leaps
to get where he's going, Ian?

10:07.694 --> 10:12.089
- I would say no less than ten,
but probably closer to 20.

10:12.133 --> 10:14.004
- So he's not coming home
anytime soon?

10:14.048 --> 10:15.745
- That's what I've been
trying to tell you.

10:15.789 --> 10:18.095
- Okay.
I have to tell him.

10:18.139 --> 10:22.665
- Addison,
we don't know how he'll react.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.275
- He'll react like Ben.

10:24.319 --> 10:25.973
He might have lost his memory,
but he's still the same man.

10:26.016 --> 10:27.931
He'll adapt.
He'll be strong.

10:27.975 --> 10:29.367
I'll tell him
after he wins the fight,

10:29.411 --> 10:31.935
which, speaking of,
I have a lot of work to do,

10:31.979 --> 10:33.937
so unless you need me here--

10:33.981 --> 10:37.941
- Go ahead.
- Thank you.

10:37.985 --> 10:39.856
- Where are we going?
[slot machines chiming]

10:39.900 --> 10:42.903
- Out the side entrance.
Avoid you being crowded.

10:42.946 --> 10:45.470
- Daryl, we need to delay
the fight, one week, maybe two.

10:45.514 --> 10:47.821
- I'm just not feeling well.
- That's just nerves.

10:47.864 --> 10:49.953
- It's not.
You saw me earlier.

10:49.997 --> 10:51.651
I almost got knocked out
by my own sparring partner.

10:51.694 --> 10:53.304
- Hey, keep your voice down.

10:53.348 --> 10:57.961
Look, the promoter,
he has a out in your contract.

10:58.005 --> 10:59.833
Any delay, he moves on.

10:59.876 --> 11:02.313
Little brother, there's
a whole line of fighters

11:02.357 --> 11:04.228
waiting for their shot,
a line we jumped

11:04.272 --> 11:06.187
because I called in every favor
I was owed.

11:06.230 --> 11:09.016
Now you really wanna wait years
for another chance?

11:09.059 --> 11:10.452
- It's better than losing.

11:10.495 --> 11:12.323
- How about losing the gym?

11:12.367 --> 11:13.542
- What?

11:13.585 --> 11:15.587
[tense music]

11:15.631 --> 11:17.546
- Go on, get in the car.

11:17.589 --> 11:23.508
♪

11:23.552 --> 11:27.077
- This is Ben calling Addison.

11:27.121 --> 11:28.513
Addison.

11:28.557 --> 11:30.124
- Hey, champ.
He's right here.

11:30.167 --> 11:31.473
- You think
I wouldn't find out?

11:31.516 --> 11:33.127
You think I didn't know?

11:33.170 --> 11:35.390
I followed her this morning.

11:35.433 --> 11:37.566
I saw you with Angela
with my own eyes.

11:37.609 --> 11:42.702
- Look, you hit me now,
you lose your payday.

11:42.745 --> 11:44.704
- How about
I beat your ass twice?

11:44.747 --> 11:45.705
[engine revving]

11:45.748 --> 11:47.794
[tires screeching]

11:47.837 --> 11:49.796
- Danny, get in.

11:49.839 --> 11:52.276
♪

11:52.320 --> 11:53.800
He bait you into
throwing a punch?

11:53.843 --> 11:55.932
- No, I'm good.

11:55.976 --> 11:59.153
♪

11:59.196 --> 12:02.504
- Saved by the baby killer.

12:02.547 --> 12:04.419
- Daryl, Daryl,
what are you doing?

12:04.462 --> 12:06.290
- I was serving my country
in Vietnam.

12:06.334 --> 12:07.683
You gonna stand there
and call me that?

12:07.727 --> 12:08.771
- What's the matter?

12:08.815 --> 12:09.946
A little too close
to the truth?

12:09.990 --> 12:12.862
[dramatic music]

12:12.906 --> 12:15.473
♪

12:15.517 --> 12:17.214
- Daryl, it's me, it's me!

12:17.258 --> 12:19.477
We gotta go.
We gotta go!

12:19.521 --> 12:21.479
[engine revving
and tires screeching]

12:21.523 --> 12:23.220
- [shouts]

12:23.264 --> 12:26.528
♪

12:27.616 --> 12:29.444
- That was crazy.

12:29.487 --> 12:32.403
[suspenseful music]

12:32.447 --> 12:34.754
♪

12:34.797 --> 12:37.800
What did you mean,
lose the gym?

12:37.844 --> 12:40.803
♪

12:40.847 --> 12:43.893
Daryl, do we keep
secrets from each other?

12:43.937 --> 12:45.242
[electronic chiming]

12:45.286 --> 12:47.201
- Okay, Ben, I know everything
there is to know

12:47.244 --> 12:48.768
about your fight
with the champ.

12:48.811 --> 12:50.247
Hey.

12:50.291 --> 12:52.510
♪

12:52.554 --> 12:54.034
- Oh, okay.

12:54.077 --> 12:55.557
Okay, okay, we're not gonna
talk about any of it, huh?

12:55.600 --> 12:56.906
Is that the way you want me
going into the fight?

12:56.950 --> 12:58.603
Distracted?

12:58.647 --> 13:04.958
♪

13:05.001 --> 13:08.831
- We ran out of money
eight months ago.

13:08.875 --> 13:13.009
I had to borrow
against the gym.

13:13.053 --> 13:16.447
Banks turned me down, so...

13:16.491 --> 13:18.972
I went to the sharks.

13:19.015 --> 13:21.801
Penny doesn't know...

13:21.844 --> 13:23.846
and I didn't want you
to either.

13:23.890 --> 13:26.066
Look, I'm your older brother.

13:26.109 --> 13:27.241
My job is to shelter you

13:27.284 --> 13:29.460
from all the ugliness
in this world.

13:29.504 --> 13:30.810
♪

13:30.853 --> 13:33.247
Keep your chin up, okay?

13:33.290 --> 13:35.640
'Cause none of this will matter
when you win tomorrow night.

13:35.684 --> 13:39.122
- What if I lose?

13:39.166 --> 13:40.471
- I told you
don't ever say that.

13:40.515 --> 13:42.996
- What if I lose?

13:43.039 --> 13:45.650
Will you be able to sell
the gym and pay them back?

13:45.694 --> 13:49.829
♪

13:49.872 --> 13:51.743
- I want 15 minutes of rope.

13:51.787 --> 13:53.354
Work the speed bag.

13:53.397 --> 13:56.400
Nothing too hard.

13:56.444 --> 13:57.532
[door slams]

13:57.575 --> 13:59.926
♪

13:59.969 --> 14:01.101
- I don't think
this is just about

14:01.144 --> 14:03.930
winning a fight, Addison.

14:03.973 --> 14:05.670
- Yeah.

14:05.714 --> 14:09.631
♪

14:09.674 --> 14:12.329
How did Ziggy miss this?

14:12.373 --> 14:15.376
- Miss what?

14:15.419 --> 14:18.335
- After Danny loses the fight,
Daryl's forced to sell the gym.

14:18.379 --> 14:21.991
With his debts mounting up,
he--

14:22.035 --> 14:23.863
he took his own life, Ben.

14:23.906 --> 14:29.607
I think you're here
to save him.

14:35.004 --> 14:36.266
- I know what he's doing.

14:36.310 --> 14:37.789
That is the course
that "Voyager 2"

14:37.833 --> 14:39.313
took through our solar system.

14:39.356 --> 14:41.576
Now you see how it slingshots
around the inner planets?

14:41.619 --> 14:43.143
That's called gravity-assisted
navigation.

14:43.186 --> 14:45.101
It's the only way
the "Voyager 2" could speed up

14:45.145 --> 14:49.932
enough in order
to reach the outer planets.

14:49.976 --> 14:51.978
- Okay?
And what is this have to do--

14:52.021 --> 14:54.328
- I think that Ben is trying
to do the same thing,

14:54.371 --> 14:56.808
but through time.

14:56.852 --> 14:58.898
He's moving from point to point

14:58.941 --> 15:00.856
in order
to build up enough momentum

15:00.900 --> 15:02.510
so that he could leap further

15:02.553 --> 15:03.685
than would otherwise
be possible.

15:03.728 --> 15:05.774
- If you're right, it means...

15:05.817 --> 15:09.604
Ben could leap as far back
in time as he wanted.

15:09.647 --> 15:11.171
- Ian, what are you doing?

15:11.214 --> 15:13.738
I need you down there working,
not up here playing genius.

15:13.782 --> 15:15.175
Have you figured out
what's up with Ziggy?

15:15.218 --> 15:16.393
- What are you talking about?

15:16.437 --> 15:18.004
- I told you before.
Ziggy seemed slow.

15:18.047 --> 15:21.094
Now it just missed the
entire reason for Ben's leap.

15:21.137 --> 15:23.531
Something's wrong.

15:23.574 --> 15:25.533
- Okay, so you were right.

15:25.576 --> 15:26.969
Something is
slowing Ziggy down.

15:27.013 --> 15:29.232
- How long to figure out
what's wrong?

15:29.276 --> 15:30.799
- I don't know.

15:30.842 --> 15:33.410
I built a firewall around
the computational center

15:33.454 --> 15:35.935
while it troubleshoots,
but until I can figure it out,

15:35.978 --> 15:38.981
Ziggy's performance might be
a little compromised at times.

15:39.025 --> 15:42.550
- Let me know the minute
you find out what happened.

15:42.593 --> 15:44.944
[soft dramatic music]

15:44.987 --> 15:47.511
♪

15:47.555 --> 15:49.296
- I'm sorry I snapped earlier.

15:49.339 --> 15:52.952
Being a hologram
is frustrating.

15:52.995 --> 15:53.996
♪

15:54.040 --> 15:57.173
I can't protect him,
I can't--

15:57.217 --> 15:59.871
watching from the sidelines
has never been my strong suit.

15:59.915 --> 16:01.830
- [chuckles]

16:01.873 --> 16:04.050
- Yeah, no, I--
I get it.

16:04.093 --> 16:05.747
Trust me.
I do.

16:05.790 --> 16:07.749
And I also think
you might just be

16:07.792 --> 16:10.099
underestimating the power
of being a hologram.

16:10.143 --> 16:11.753
I mean, you might not
be able to hit somebody,

16:11.796 --> 16:15.713
but you could, for example,
shadow box.

16:15.757 --> 16:18.673
[soft upbeat music]

16:18.716 --> 16:24.157
♪

16:24.200 --> 16:25.636
- Looking good.

16:25.680 --> 16:27.421
- Okay, we have got
to work on your entrances,

16:27.464 --> 16:29.423
maybe get you a bike bell.

16:29.466 --> 16:32.513
- A bike bell?
How about a bullhorn?

16:32.556 --> 16:33.818
[door opens]

16:35.124 --> 16:36.908
Penny Hill, Daryl's wife.

16:36.952 --> 16:41.957
- Hey, Penny.
Daryl's in his office.

16:42.001 --> 16:46.701
- I actually came to see you.

16:48.007 --> 16:50.661
- What's wrong with my husband?

16:50.705 --> 16:53.969
I don't even
recognize him anymore.

16:54.013 --> 16:57.059
The way he talks,
the way he looks at me,

16:57.103 --> 17:01.585
it's like...everything
that we had just disappeared.

17:01.629 --> 17:04.632
- He's been under
a lot of pressure,

17:04.675 --> 17:08.636
and he's been keeping it
to himself to protect us.

17:08.679 --> 17:11.465
- He tries to hide it, but...

17:11.508 --> 17:15.469
anyone can see he is...

17:15.512 --> 17:19.864
carrying the weight
of the world.

17:19.908 --> 17:23.303
I just wish that he would
talk to me about it,

17:23.346 --> 17:26.654
talk to anyone.

17:26.697 --> 17:29.048
- I think tomorrow if--

17:29.091 --> 17:31.876
whenI win,

17:31.920 --> 17:34.227
all of that pressure
should lift.

17:34.270 --> 17:37.491
- That'll be good.

17:37.534 --> 17:39.623
Your brother could use a break.

17:39.667 --> 17:43.410
Seems like ever since
his tour was over,

17:43.453 --> 17:45.238
been nothing but bad luck.

17:45.281 --> 17:47.588
[soft dramatic music]

17:47.631 --> 17:49.155
♪

17:49.198 --> 17:51.157
Well, I'll let you
get back to it.

17:51.200 --> 17:52.636
[sniffles]

17:52.680 --> 17:55.509
♪

17:55.552 --> 17:58.338
In case either of you
are hungry.

17:58.381 --> 17:59.339
Good night, Danny.

17:59.382 --> 18:01.993
♪

18:02.037 --> 18:04.692
[door opens]

18:04.735 --> 18:06.955
[door closes]
- This is hard, Addison.

18:06.998 --> 18:09.653
I know I'm not Danny
and I know I should not care,

18:09.697 --> 18:11.002
but this is not so easy.

18:11.046 --> 18:12.308
- I know.

18:12.352 --> 18:14.571
Trust me.

18:14.615 --> 18:16.921
- We need to win.
How do we do that?

18:16.965 --> 18:18.140
- Funny you should ask.

18:18.184 --> 18:21.143
So I have been thinking
you might be Ben,

18:21.187 --> 18:23.058
but you have leapt
into the body

18:23.102 --> 18:25.713
of a professional fighter,
a body that's strong,

18:25.756 --> 18:27.758
a body that is trained
and lightning fast.

18:27.802 --> 18:30.587
When you hit,
it's not Ben's fist

18:30.631 --> 18:32.111
Roy Gordon's going to feel.

18:32.154 --> 18:33.373
It's Danny's.

18:33.416 --> 18:35.636
Roy Gordon's gonna feel that.

18:35.679 --> 18:38.813
- So physically,
I have Danny's conditioning.

18:38.856 --> 18:40.728
I have his strength
and his speed.

18:40.771 --> 18:42.773
I just have to harness it.
- Exactly.

18:42.817 --> 18:45.385
- The problem is I don't
have the skill or experience,

18:45.428 --> 18:48.649
so I don't know what to do
once the fight starts.

18:48.692 --> 18:50.172
- [sighing] Yeah.

18:50.216 --> 18:52.174
If only there was
a way to know exactly

18:52.218 --> 18:54.045
what the champ would do.

18:54.089 --> 18:58.398
If we could see the fight
before it happened--

18:58.441 --> 19:01.183
oh, wait.

19:01.227 --> 19:02.663
What do we have here?

19:02.706 --> 19:05.274
- Do you wanna milk that moment
a little bit longer?

19:05.318 --> 19:06.841
Should I give you
some more time with that?

19:06.884 --> 19:08.538
- You know, I really gotta
get the wins where I can.

19:08.582 --> 19:10.105
Okay...

19:10.149 --> 19:12.325
you have a photographic memory.

19:12.368 --> 19:15.415
- I do.
Ironic.

19:15.458 --> 19:17.808
- Let's put it to use.

19:18.983 --> 19:21.595
- My.
You found all this so fast.

19:21.638 --> 19:23.684
- Magic is me.
- [chuckles]

19:23.727 --> 19:25.468
Headlines.

19:25.512 --> 19:29.037
- Ben's been working on his new
code for the past six months.

19:29.080 --> 19:32.519
- Six months?
That can't be right.

19:32.562 --> 19:33.607
- Remember the
physics symposium

19:33.650 --> 19:35.348
he went to in San Diego?

19:35.391 --> 19:38.177
He got there,
but he left two days early.

19:38.220 --> 19:40.570
I found more than two dozen
other inconsistencies

19:40.614 --> 19:42.006
since then.

19:42.050 --> 19:43.660
I'm gonna have
to interview Addison,

19:43.704 --> 19:45.184
ask her about every day
since San Diego.

19:45.227 --> 19:47.838
And she's gonna feel
every single lie.

19:47.882 --> 19:50.058
♪

19:50.101 --> 19:51.799
[cheers and applause]

19:51.842 --> 19:53.714
[dramatic music]

19:53.757 --> 19:55.411
- Okay,
Ziggy ran the scenarios.

19:55.455 --> 19:58.458
The best time to strike is when
Gordon gives up an opportunity

19:58.501 --> 19:59.502
in the second round.

19:59.546 --> 20:00.982
That's what Danny missed.

20:01.025 --> 20:02.897
- So I just have to make
it to the second round

20:02.940 --> 20:05.160
without deviating
from the original history.

20:05.204 --> 20:06.988
- Yeah, but the fight
has to play out

20:07.031 --> 20:09.947
exactly like it did
to get to that opening.

20:09.991 --> 20:12.515
Every step, every feint,
every punch.

20:12.559 --> 20:16.258
♪

20:16.302 --> 20:18.391
- Every punch?

20:18.434 --> 20:19.870
- Don't joke.

20:19.914 --> 20:21.916
You have to execute
all of those moves perfectly,

20:21.959 --> 20:23.483
or you are on your own

20:23.526 --> 20:25.224
against the middleweight
champion of the world.

20:25.267 --> 20:27.226
[fist thumps]
- [groans]

20:27.269 --> 20:34.189
♪

20:38.541 --> 20:40.891
- Okay.
Let's go to work.

20:40.935 --> 20:42.980
♪

20:43.024 --> 20:45.331
[countdown chimes beeping]

20:45.374 --> 20:46.332
♪

20:46.375 --> 20:47.594
[buzzer]

20:47.637 --> 20:49.291
- All right, let's go again.

20:49.335 --> 20:50.510
♪

20:50.553 --> 20:53.513
[countdown chimes beeping]

20:53.556 --> 20:54.862
[buzzer]

20:54.905 --> 20:56.864
- I'm a righty,
Danny's a lefty.

20:56.907 --> 20:58.257
Everything about this
feels off.

20:58.300 --> 20:59.867
- Then we run it
and we run it again

20:59.910 --> 21:01.085
until it feels right.

21:01.129 --> 21:04.132
Let's go.
[countdown chimes beeping]

21:04.175 --> 21:05.525
[buzzer]
- [groans]

21:05.568 --> 21:06.700
- Again.
Come on.

21:06.743 --> 21:08.789
[countdown chimes beeping]
Yup.

21:08.832 --> 21:09.833
♪

21:09.877 --> 21:11.182
[buzzer]
That's the hook!

21:11.226 --> 21:12.793
- [grunting]

21:12.836 --> 21:13.794
[buzzers]

21:13.837 --> 21:14.838
- Keep that right up.

21:14.882 --> 21:16.144
Dude, that's a jab!
Come on!

21:16.187 --> 21:17.493
Now he's coming at you.
Ben, that's wrong.

21:17.537 --> 21:18.581
One, two.
Now come on.

21:18.625 --> 21:19.539
Let him hit you with the left.

21:19.582 --> 21:20.540
Again.

21:20.583 --> 21:21.541
Again.

21:21.584 --> 21:22.759
Again!

21:22.803 --> 21:24.892
Ben!

21:24.935 --> 21:26.328
- Addison, you okay?

21:26.372 --> 21:28.504
It's just a little--
- Let's do it again.

21:28.548 --> 21:29.592
- We're taking a break.

21:29.636 --> 21:30.767
- You don't have time
for a break!

21:30.811 --> 21:33.379
- I'm not asking.
You're clearly exhausted.

21:33.422 --> 21:34.728
We need to stop.

21:34.771 --> 21:37.905
- You can't afford to stop,
and neither can I.

21:37.948 --> 21:40.560
I have to be here
all of the time.

21:40.603 --> 21:41.778
Do you understand that?

21:41.822 --> 21:44.955
I cannot let you
make a single mistake,

21:44.999 --> 21:47.523
or else we're done.

21:47.567 --> 21:50.918
It's over.
You fail.

21:50.961 --> 21:53.399
And you never get home.

21:53.442 --> 21:54.748
You never get--
[electric thrumming]

21:54.791 --> 21:55.792
- Addison.

21:55.836 --> 21:57.011
Addison!

21:57.751 --> 22:00.231
[tense music]

22:05.324 --> 22:08.239
[electronic chiming]

22:08.283 --> 22:11.199
[soft dramatic music]

22:11.242 --> 22:13.810
♪

22:13.854 --> 22:15.551
- What happened?

22:15.595 --> 22:18.772
- You lost consciousness
in the imaging chamber.

22:18.815 --> 22:21.905
Doc says you're suffering from
exhaustion and dehydration.

22:21.949 --> 22:23.733
You scared the hell
out of all of us.

22:23.777 --> 22:25.648
- I feel fine.
Really.

22:25.692 --> 22:29.870
- No, no.
Doc says you have to rest.

22:29.913 --> 22:32.176
- [sighs]
How long?

22:32.220 --> 22:34.091
- She wanted two days.
- I can't.

22:34.135 --> 22:36.659
- I told her she'd
be lucky to get two hours.

22:36.703 --> 22:39.401
Now electrolytes,
vitamins, fluids,

22:39.445 --> 22:41.708
enough to get you
through this sleep.

22:41.751 --> 22:44.406
When it's finished,
you can get up.

22:44.450 --> 22:46.016
Any sooner,
you're gonna collapse again

22:46.060 --> 22:47.627
and help no one.

22:47.670 --> 22:50.369
Now that we know Ben
is going somewhere

22:50.412 --> 22:52.109
and he's leaping his way
to get there,

22:52.153 --> 22:55.112
we have to treat this like
a marathon and not a sprint.

22:55.156 --> 22:58.246
♪

22:58.289 --> 23:00.422
[keyboard clicking]

23:00.466 --> 23:02.119
[computer chiming]

23:02.163 --> 23:04.687
- Jenn!

23:04.731 --> 23:05.993
- That doesn't sound good.

23:06.036 --> 23:07.951
- Well, I found out
why Ziggy's running slow.

23:07.995 --> 23:11.259
Someone opened a remote link
into the system.

23:11.302 --> 23:12.608
- Janis Calavicci.

23:12.652 --> 23:16.003
[doorbell chimes]

23:16.046 --> 23:18.222
- Hi, Mom.
- How did she do it?

23:18.266 --> 23:20.094
- Best guess, Trojan Horse
on the drive we found

23:20.137 --> 23:21.965
at Addison and Ben's place.

23:22.009 --> 23:24.098
It's looking more and more
like Ben is being used

23:24.141 --> 23:25.839
and doesn't know it.

23:25.882 --> 23:28.363
- Ian, can we separate
Janis's connection?

23:28.407 --> 23:30.017
- I'm working on it.

23:30.060 --> 23:31.671
- They pulled surveillance
yesterday.

23:31.714 --> 23:33.542
No one's watching anymore.

23:33.586 --> 23:36.632
- That doesn't mean
they're not looking for you.

23:36.676 --> 23:38.286
What are you doing here?

23:38.329 --> 23:39.679
- I haven't seen you
in so long,

23:39.722 --> 23:42.333
and I wanted to talk.

23:42.377 --> 23:45.075
- This is kind of you.

23:45.119 --> 23:46.250
But is T okay?

23:46.294 --> 23:48.035
- Sure.

23:48.078 --> 23:49.645
I'll start the water.

23:49.689 --> 23:52.996
[suspenseful music]

23:53.040 --> 23:54.824
- Well, if I initialize
the system reboot,

23:54.868 --> 23:56.652
we might be able
to lock her out,

23:56.696 --> 23:58.219
but we'll also
lose contact with Ben.

23:58.262 --> 23:59.481
- For how long?

23:59.525 --> 24:00.961
- Reboot could take a week
or longer,

24:01.004 --> 24:02.484
which means
Ben loses the fight

24:02.528 --> 24:04.225
and he'll likely be trapped
in the past.

24:04.268 --> 24:07.141
- No, leave the system as-is.

24:07.184 --> 24:08.838
See if we can figure out
what Janis is doing.

24:08.882 --> 24:10.492
- Oh, she can't
really do anything.

24:10.536 --> 24:11.841
She can access data,

24:11.885 --> 24:14.540
but it's not like
she can send commands to Ziggy.

24:14.583 --> 24:17.020
She doesn't have the tech
to interface with it.

24:17.064 --> 24:18.239
♪

24:18.282 --> 24:19.675
- I don't know
why I never thought of it.

24:19.719 --> 24:21.938
All these years,
I blamed Magic

24:21.982 --> 24:25.464
for banning me
from the QL program.

24:25.507 --> 24:27.509
And it was you.

24:27.553 --> 24:30.686
You asked him to do it,
didn't you?

24:30.730 --> 24:32.645
- I did what I had to do.

24:32.688 --> 24:34.864
You would have spent your
life chasing phantoms,

24:34.908 --> 24:37.127
wasted your brilliant mind
on a program

24:37.171 --> 24:38.738
that was never going to work.

24:38.781 --> 24:42.829
Sam Beckett was lost forever.
Your dad never got over it.

24:42.872 --> 24:45.048
Is it so wrong for me
to want to protect you

24:45.092 --> 24:46.223
from that same fate?

24:46.267 --> 24:49.400
- No, it isn't wrong.

24:49.444 --> 24:52.447
[soft dramatic music]

24:52.491 --> 24:55.232
I do have one question though.

24:55.276 --> 24:57.757
♪

24:57.800 --> 25:02.413
Did it ever occur to you
that maybe I wouldn't fail?

25:02.457 --> 25:04.851
Did you ever once consider

25:04.894 --> 25:06.548
that maybe your daughter
was smart enough

25:06.592 --> 25:09.551
to succeed where
everyone else went wrong,

25:09.595 --> 25:11.640
that I was the only one
talented enough

25:11.684 --> 25:14.251
to make all of dad's dreams
come true?

25:14.295 --> 25:17.472
♪

25:17.516 --> 25:20.170
Wow.

25:20.214 --> 25:21.911
♪

25:21.955 --> 25:25.001
Didn't think so.

25:25.045 --> 25:28.178
♪

25:28.222 --> 25:30.659
It's okay.

25:30.703 --> 25:32.095
Water under the bridge.

25:32.139 --> 25:34.271
I would, however,
in light of your admission,

25:34.315 --> 25:36.273
I would like to collect
all of my father's things

25:36.317 --> 25:38.711
relating to the program.

25:38.754 --> 25:41.714
- I'm sorry, Janis.

25:41.757 --> 25:43.063
I can't let you have them.

25:43.106 --> 25:44.673
- Even though
you just admitted

25:44.717 --> 25:47.894
that you unjustly
sabotaged my entire career.

25:47.937 --> 25:52.594
- I don't believe
it was unjust.

25:52.638 --> 25:55.989
And I am not going
to change my mind.

25:56.032 --> 25:59.862
♪

25:59.906 --> 26:03.344
Janis, what did you do me?

26:03.387 --> 26:05.607
[suspenseful music]

26:05.651 --> 26:08.088
- I did what I had to do.

26:10.612 --> 26:12.005
- Ring, ring.

26:12.048 --> 26:13.136
- [sighs]

26:13.180 --> 26:14.268
- What?

26:14.311 --> 26:16.487
That's my imitation
of a bike bell.

26:16.531 --> 26:18.054
- Thank God.
- [chuckles]

26:18.098 --> 26:19.621
- Are you okay?
- I'm totally fine.

26:19.665 --> 26:21.101
- Are you sure?

26:21.144 --> 26:22.581
because when you collapsed,
I tried to catch you,

26:22.624 --> 26:25.584
and I couldn't and it--
- And it sucks.

26:25.627 --> 26:29.152
Yeah, well,
welcome to my world.

26:31.285 --> 26:32.416
How's it going?

26:32.460 --> 26:36.638
- So I'm here, boom, right?
- Right.

26:36.682 --> 26:38.814
- I come along this way.

26:38.858 --> 26:41.512
- Why are you
fighting right-handed?

26:41.556 --> 26:44.907
- Oh, just pulling out
all the stops,

26:44.951 --> 26:46.866
doing whatever I can to win.

26:50.043 --> 26:51.610
- Penny came by?

26:51.653 --> 26:53.612
- Yeah, she just wanted
to drop those off

26:53.655 --> 26:55.091
in case we got hungry.

26:55.135 --> 26:57.703
- But she ain't wanna
talk to me, huh?

26:57.746 --> 26:59.530
'Cause she wanna talk to you?

26:59.574 --> 27:00.967
You know, let me guess.

27:01.010 --> 27:03.839
She's worried about me.
Am I right?

27:03.883 --> 27:04.971
You know that's the
story she's been

27:05.014 --> 27:06.712
spinning to all my friends?

27:06.755 --> 27:09.323
Going behind my back!

27:09.366 --> 27:10.846
Telling people my business.

27:10.890 --> 27:13.588
- Man, I've seen this before.
This is PTSD.

27:13.632 --> 27:15.677
- I know.
- You don't know!

27:15.721 --> 27:18.637
[soft dramatic music]

27:18.680 --> 27:20.900
♪

27:20.943 --> 27:22.684
- A lot of the people
I served with in Afghanistan

27:22.728 --> 27:25.948
came home with some sort
of emotional trauma,

27:25.992 --> 27:27.863
but at least
there are treatments now.

27:27.907 --> 27:30.692
- Daryl, listen to me.

27:30.736 --> 27:32.215
You need help.

27:32.259 --> 27:35.175
[sirens wailing]

27:35.218 --> 27:37.786
Daryl, stay calm.
I can handle this.

27:37.830 --> 27:40.180
[knocking at door]

27:40.223 --> 27:41.398
- Is Mr. Daryl Hill here?

27:41.442 --> 27:43.183
- The hell you want?

27:43.226 --> 27:44.575
- Mr. Hill,
you're under arrest

27:44.619 --> 27:46.795
for the assault of Sean Willis
and Charles White.

27:46.839 --> 27:48.710
- That was self-defense,
officer.

27:48.754 --> 27:50.320
He was protecting me.

27:50.364 --> 27:51.321
- Step aside.

27:51.365 --> 27:54.281
[dramatic music]

27:54.324 --> 27:55.325
♪

27:55.369 --> 27:56.718
- Ben, you need
to keep him calm.

27:56.762 --> 27:58.067
- Daryl, just breathe.

27:58.111 --> 27:59.460
- Okay, tell him that
he's not alone.

27:59.503 --> 28:00.722
- Daryl,
I'm right here with you.

28:00.766 --> 28:02.419
- Get him to look at you.
- Daryl, look at me.

28:02.463 --> 28:04.073
Look at me!

28:04.117 --> 28:05.988
We're gonna get through this.

28:06.032 --> 28:07.424
We're gonna get through this

28:07.468 --> 28:09.992
the same way we've gotten
through everything before.

28:10.036 --> 28:13.779
Together.

28:13.822 --> 28:20.960
♪

28:25.965 --> 28:28.445
That's why Danny
was distracted.

28:28.489 --> 28:29.751
- Yes.

28:29.795 --> 28:31.535
Ziggy says there
was a fight in jail.

28:31.579 --> 28:32.667
He's locked up for 72 hours.

28:32.711 --> 28:34.408
- Missing the fight.
- Yeah.

28:34.451 --> 28:36.671
- Something's gotta change.

28:36.715 --> 28:38.629
- Hey, pigs!
Forget about me?

28:38.673 --> 28:40.588
- What did you call me?

28:40.631 --> 28:42.633
[tense music]

28:42.677 --> 28:44.113
- Take him, too.

28:44.157 --> 28:48.727
♪

28:48.770 --> 28:50.337
- How is this an improvement?

28:55.864 --> 28:58.171
- Ziggy says
your little gambit worked.

28:58.214 --> 29:00.347
You both get out of jail
now, but--

29:00.390 --> 29:02.610
but Daryl still
takes his own life.

29:02.653 --> 29:05.744
It just happens
a few months later.

29:05.787 --> 29:08.137
- It'll happen even if I win,
won't it?

29:08.181 --> 29:09.791
- There's no way
for Ziggy to know that.

29:09.835 --> 29:11.401
- Not asking Ziggy.

29:11.445 --> 29:14.361
[soft dramatic music]

29:14.404 --> 29:16.798
♪

29:16.842 --> 29:19.670
- Without help, yeah,
it probably will.

29:19.714 --> 29:20.933
♪

29:20.976 --> 29:22.369
[door opens]

29:22.412 --> 29:28.505
♪

29:28.549 --> 29:30.812
- Hill brothers,
congratulations.

29:30.856 --> 29:32.335
You made bail.

29:37.427 --> 29:39.603
- Last I checked,
we got a fight to win.

29:39.647 --> 29:41.823
- No.

29:41.867 --> 29:44.652
I'm not fighting unless
you promise to see a doctor.

29:44.695 --> 29:46.480
- [scoffs]

29:46.523 --> 29:47.916
Man,
you sound like Penny, man.

29:47.960 --> 29:49.875
- I'm serious, Daryl.

29:49.918 --> 29:51.180
I'm not walking out of here
unless you promise--

29:51.224 --> 29:53.313
- I don't need help.

29:53.356 --> 29:54.749
- You nearly went off
on those cops.

29:54.793 --> 29:55.619
- But I didn't.

29:55.663 --> 29:56.751
- And you got out of the car

29:56.795 --> 29:59.710
when we could have just
driven away.

29:59.754 --> 30:02.322
- [exhales deeply]

30:02.365 --> 30:04.803
What's a doctor gonna do
for me?

30:04.846 --> 30:08.371
Give me some pills
to help me sleep?

30:08.415 --> 30:11.113
The doctor can't fix
what I got, man.

30:11.157 --> 30:13.507
♪

30:13.550 --> 30:15.857
Every time I close my eyes,

30:15.901 --> 30:19.295
I see bodies,

30:19.339 --> 30:21.994
men that I served with.

30:22.037 --> 30:25.867
You think I wanna
to be going off?

30:25.911 --> 30:29.697
Yelling at my wife?

30:29.740 --> 30:31.264
[sniffles]

30:31.307 --> 30:33.179
♪

30:33.222 --> 30:35.224
[chuckles]

30:35.268 --> 30:37.836
I don't know how
to be her husband anymore.

30:37.879 --> 30:40.534
♪

30:40.577 --> 30:42.666
I don't even know
why I'm still here, man.

30:42.710 --> 30:44.712
[sobbing softly]

30:44.755 --> 30:49.282
- Because Ineed you.

30:49.325 --> 30:51.893
You said I can't afford
to be distracted.

30:51.937 --> 30:53.808
How am I supposed
to win a damn fight

30:53.852 --> 30:57.899
when I know my brother,
my only family, is losing his?

30:57.943 --> 30:59.770
[soft delicate music]

30:59.814 --> 31:01.033
You think
I care about a title

31:01.076 --> 31:04.558
if I don't have you around
to share it with?

31:04.601 --> 31:09.519
Man, you taught me
everything I know.

31:09.563 --> 31:12.740
Everything I have
is because of you.

31:12.783 --> 31:17.353
♪

31:17.397 --> 31:18.398
[sniffles]

31:18.441 --> 31:19.703
And I been waiting 25 years

31:19.747 --> 31:22.663
to prove I'm a better fighter
than you.

31:22.706 --> 31:24.883
You better believe I'm gonna
wrap that belt around me

31:24.926 --> 31:28.364
and walk all up and down
your living room every day,

31:28.408 --> 31:29.931
show it off right in your face.

31:29.975 --> 31:32.586
- [chuckling]

31:32.629 --> 31:35.850
Man, you got me
crying in here.

31:35.894 --> 31:37.460
Crying.

31:37.504 --> 31:39.767
Oh, get it together.

31:39.810 --> 31:43.597
Okay, I promise.

31:43.640 --> 31:45.033
I'll go.

31:45.077 --> 31:47.470
- And you'll keep going,

31:47.514 --> 31:50.082
and you won't quit
no matter what.

31:50.125 --> 31:51.431
♪

31:51.474 --> 31:53.215
- If you win the fight.

31:53.259 --> 31:55.826
- Not if...

31:55.870 --> 31:57.089
when.

31:57.132 --> 32:04.009
♪

32:08.143 --> 32:11.103
[soft upbeat music]

32:11.146 --> 32:14.280
♪

32:14.323 --> 32:16.935
- [giggles]

32:16.978 --> 32:19.241
♪

32:19.285 --> 32:20.242
- Thank you, darling.

32:20.286 --> 32:21.722
- Don't thank me.

32:21.765 --> 32:23.463
- She's the one that paid.

32:23.506 --> 32:26.205
♪

32:26.248 --> 32:27.249
- Thank you, Angela.

32:27.293 --> 32:29.643
- You're welcome.

32:29.686 --> 32:33.212
I love your brother.
You know that, right?

32:33.255 --> 32:35.040
- Yeah.

32:35.083 --> 32:38.043
- And you can thank me tonight

32:38.086 --> 32:40.262
by knocking
that ugly son of a bitch out.

32:40.306 --> 32:43.004
[laughter]

32:43.048 --> 32:44.136
- Hell, yeah.

32:44.179 --> 32:45.441
- I know you got soul!

32:45.485 --> 32:47.835
One, two, three, hit it!

32:47.878 --> 32:50.098
[Bobby Byrd's
"I Know You Got Soul"]

32:50.142 --> 32:51.752
[cheers and applause]

32:51.795 --> 32:54.842
- ♪ You got it, you got it,
you got it ♪

32:54.885 --> 32:57.279
♪ You got it,
I know you got soul ♪

32:57.323 --> 33:00.848
[cheers and applause]

33:00.891 --> 33:02.023
- You okay?

33:02.067 --> 33:03.982
- The Champ's
only got one trainer.

33:04.025 --> 33:07.333
I've got two.

33:07.376 --> 33:10.031
- Boxers, center.

33:10.075 --> 33:11.511
♪

33:11.554 --> 33:12.991
Gentlemen, I've given
your instructions in the back.

33:13.034 --> 33:14.731
Touch them up.
Back to your corner.

33:14.775 --> 33:17.473
[cheers and applause]

33:17.517 --> 33:18.997
- Come on, baby!

33:19.040 --> 33:20.911
[bell rings]

33:20.955 --> 33:22.043
♪

33:22.087 --> 33:25.090
- Okay, Ben,
just like we practiced.

33:25.133 --> 33:30.573
♪

33:30.617 --> 33:32.010
- ♪ I know you got soul

33:32.053 --> 33:33.054
♪

33:33.098 --> 33:35.100
[bell rings]

33:35.143 --> 33:36.449
- You're doing great, Ben.

33:36.492 --> 33:38.016
It is lining up perfectly
with the original fight.

33:38.059 --> 33:39.887
- What are doing out there?
You leaving yourself open.

33:39.930 --> 33:41.367
- No, I've got him
right where I want him.

33:41.410 --> 33:42.629
Next round, he's going down.

33:42.672 --> 33:44.587
[cheers and applause]

33:44.631 --> 33:48.069
- You got this, baby!
- Let's go!

33:48.113 --> 33:50.289
- Okay, remember don't deviate
until you see the opening.

33:50.332 --> 33:52.421
- Get some distance!

33:52.465 --> 33:54.728
- Yes!
- Work the body, work the body!

33:54.771 --> 33:56.860
There we go.
- That's it! Kick his ass!

33:56.904 --> 33:58.471
- Now!

33:58.514 --> 34:00.908
[dramatic music]

34:00.951 --> 34:03.563
[cheers and applause]
That's what I'm talking about!

34:03.606 --> 34:06.261
- Oh, my God!
- Yes!

34:06.305 --> 34:09.395
- One, two, three, four,

34:09.438 --> 34:14.574
five, six, seven, eight, nine.

34:14.617 --> 34:16.837
[cheers and applause]

34:16.880 --> 34:18.099
You okay?

34:18.143 --> 34:19.318
[cheers and applause]

34:19.361 --> 34:21.102
Walk to me.

34:21.146 --> 34:23.235
[upbeat funky music]

34:23.278 --> 34:26.412
- That should've worked.

34:26.455 --> 34:27.848
- It did not.

34:31.547 --> 34:33.941
[dramatic music]

34:33.984 --> 34:36.248
- Oh.

34:36.291 --> 34:38.989
[groans]
Ziggy's still running slow.

34:39.033 --> 34:40.165
We're on our own.

34:40.208 --> 34:42.123
- Thanks.
I feel much better now.

34:42.167 --> 34:43.298
Any suggestions?

34:43.342 --> 34:44.821
- You see the color
of his left eye?

34:44.865 --> 34:46.040
Stick to his right.

34:46.084 --> 34:46.954
It'll be harder
for him to track you.

34:46.997 --> 34:48.390
- Do that, do that.

34:48.434 --> 34:49.652
- You got this, baby!
You got this! Win this fight!

34:49.696 --> 34:52.090
♪

34:52.133 --> 34:53.091
- [grunts]
- Yeah!

34:53.134 --> 34:54.309
- Come on, baby.
- Yes!

34:54.353 --> 34:55.702
- Come on!
- Come on, Ben!

34:55.745 --> 34:57.095
[audience exclaiming]

34:57.138 --> 34:58.008
- Oh, God.
- Oh, my God.

34:58.052 --> 34:59.227
♪

34:59.271 --> 35:01.360
- Danny!
[high-pitched ringing]

35:01.403 --> 35:04.450
[flowing dramatic music]

35:04.493 --> 35:10.891
♪

35:10.934 --> 35:13.720
- Come on, it's time to get up.

35:13.763 --> 35:16.897
- Danny, get up now!
[words echoing]

35:16.940 --> 35:19.378
- It's time to get up.
Ben, get up.

35:19.421 --> 35:20.640
Ben, get up now!

35:20.683 --> 35:23.208
♪

35:23.251 --> 35:24.905
- Yes, yes!
- Yes, yes, come on!

35:24.948 --> 35:26.863
♪

35:26.907 --> 35:28.474
- I'm good.
- There you go.

35:28.517 --> 35:29.649
- I'm up, I'm up!

35:29.692 --> 35:31.172
- Look at me.
Are you okay to continue?

35:31.216 --> 35:32.260
- Yeah, yeah.

35:32.304 --> 35:33.392
- What's your name?
- Ben Song.

35:33.435 --> 35:35.829
I mean--I mean--
Danny, Danny Hill.

35:35.872 --> 35:38.397
- Walk to me.

35:38.440 --> 35:39.267
Box.

35:39.311 --> 35:41.574
[bell ringing]
Time.

35:41.617 --> 35:44.707
[indistinct chatter]

35:45.317 --> 35:49.190
[dramatic music]
- So much for going right.

35:49.234 --> 35:51.627
- Switch your stance.
You're right-handed.

35:51.671 --> 35:53.151
Fight that way.

35:53.194 --> 35:56.458
- You want me to fight righty?
- Yes! That could work.

35:56.502 --> 35:58.982
But look, you only gonna
get one combination

35:59.026 --> 36:00.419
before he figures it out
and counters.

36:00.462 --> 36:02.203
Slip left
to set up a straight right,

36:02.247 --> 36:05.859
flush on that chin,
you land that, we go home.

36:05.902 --> 36:07.208
♪

36:07.252 --> 36:08.818
- We go home.

36:08.862 --> 36:16.043
♪

36:27.359 --> 36:29.099
[bell ringing]
- Box.

36:29.143 --> 36:30.188
♪

36:30.231 --> 36:31.972
- Come on.

36:32.015 --> 36:39.153
♪

36:41.721 --> 36:42.852
[cheers and applause]

36:42.896 --> 36:43.940
- Fight's over.

36:43.984 --> 36:46.291
[bell ringing]
- Yes!

36:46.334 --> 36:48.684
- Oh, my God, yes!

36:48.728 --> 36:49.859
[cheers and applause]

36:49.903 --> 36:52.210
- [laughs]
You did it, little brother!

36:52.253 --> 36:53.602
You're the champion
of the world!

36:53.646 --> 36:55.474
- We did it!

36:55.517 --> 36:57.040
You're gonna get that help,
right?

36:57.084 --> 36:58.955
- I promise.

36:58.999 --> 37:01.871
I promise!
- [laughs]

37:01.915 --> 37:06.180
- The new champion
of the world, Danny Hill!

37:06.224 --> 37:09.139
[cheers and applause]

37:09.183 --> 37:10.532
- [mouths words]

37:10.576 --> 37:13.361
♪

37:13.405 --> 37:16.495
[dramatic music fading]

37:21.064 --> 37:25.547
- Well, they say a picture
is worth a thousand words.

37:25.591 --> 37:27.854
- [sighs softly]

37:27.897 --> 37:29.072
They look happy.

37:29.116 --> 37:30.378
- They are.

37:30.422 --> 37:33.425
And Daryl, once
he finishes his treatment,

37:33.468 --> 37:36.645
starts one of the first
veteran support groups for PTSD

37:36.689 --> 37:38.299
in the country.

37:38.343 --> 37:39.953
You helped a lot
of lives today, Ben.

37:39.996 --> 37:41.998
- We helped a lot
of lives today.

37:42.042 --> 37:44.958
- Yeah.
- It was a team effort.

37:45.001 --> 37:47.047
I mean,
I took all the punching.

37:47.090 --> 37:48.396
- Okay, I got knocked down,
too.

37:48.440 --> 37:50.790
Remember.
- Yeah. How could I forget?

37:50.833 --> 37:54.707
♪

37:54.750 --> 37:58.406
- Uh, look, Ben,
I gotta tell you something.

37:58.450 --> 38:00.930
It's gonna be a while
before you leap home.

38:00.974 --> 38:04.412
Your new code, it's taking
you on some kind of journey,

38:04.456 --> 38:08.373
and we don't know
where you're going

38:08.416 --> 38:11.027
and we don't know why

38:11.071 --> 38:13.682
and we don't know how many
leaps it's gonna take.

38:13.726 --> 38:17.773
♪

38:17.817 --> 38:19.297
- Oh.

38:19.340 --> 38:22.474
[soft dramatic music]

38:22.517 --> 38:23.649
Okay.

38:23.692 --> 38:27.261
♪

38:27.305 --> 38:31.961
Will you still leap with me?

38:32.005 --> 38:33.920
- Yes.

38:33.963 --> 38:35.922
I'm not going anywhere.

38:35.965 --> 38:38.490
- Then promise me
you'll take care of yourself.

38:38.533 --> 38:40.970
- Ugh, man--
- I need you, Addison.

38:41.014 --> 38:43.669
♪

38:43.712 --> 38:46.672
- Okay.

38:46.715 --> 38:50.763
♪

38:50.806 --> 38:52.634
- I almost forgot.

38:52.678 --> 38:55.376
When I got knocked out,
I remembered something.

38:55.420 --> 38:58.118
I woke up someplace,
I don't know where.

38:58.161 --> 39:01.251
Maybe my home.

39:01.295 --> 39:05.604
There was someone there.

39:05.647 --> 39:07.301
Someone I--

39:07.345 --> 39:12.480
♪

39:12.524 --> 39:15.657
[indistinct chatter on TV]

39:15.701 --> 39:17.355
♪

39:17.398 --> 39:18.704
[knock at door]

39:18.747 --> 39:25.711
♪

39:27.321 --> 39:29.323
- [chuckles]
What is happening?

39:29.367 --> 39:31.847
- We're clearly not very sorry
to barge in on you like this,

39:31.891 --> 39:34.676
but we heard that there
was a regular viewing

39:34.720 --> 39:37.244
of "Housewives" tonight,
and we thought we'd crash.

39:37.287 --> 39:38.941
- Yes,
and we brought Thai food.

39:38.985 --> 39:41.814
- And beer, but
if we're really gonna do this,

39:41.857 --> 39:44.207
I'm gonna need something
stronger. [chuckles]

39:44.251 --> 39:45.687
- I love you guys.

39:45.731 --> 39:47.210
- The feeling
is clearly mutual.

39:47.254 --> 39:49.865
You have no idea
how difficult it was

39:49.909 --> 39:51.737
for me to explain
what the show was about Magic.

39:51.780 --> 39:53.216
- [chuckles]

39:53.260 --> 39:54.566
- And Magic still doesn't
understand what it's about.

39:54.609 --> 39:57.438
- ♪ I made plans
with crooked lines ♪

39:57.482 --> 39:58.831
♪ The night feels wrong

39:58.874 --> 40:01.486
♪ When it turns out fine,
yeah ♪

40:01.529 --> 40:04.619
♪ I make time
to be a mess ♪

40:04.663 --> 40:07.100
♪ If I taste the sound
of your old address ♪

40:07.143 --> 40:10.103
[phone ringing]

40:10.146 --> 40:12.061
[tense music]

40:12.105 --> 40:14.063
[phone ringing]

40:14.107 --> 40:17.415
♪

40:17.458 --> 40:18.459
- Is she going?

40:18.503 --> 40:20.243
- No.
She came here.

40:20.287 --> 40:21.854
- What?
Why?

40:21.897 --> 40:24.726
- [sighs] Magic,
Al had some things,

40:24.770 --> 40:26.119
things he wasn't
supposed to have,

40:26.162 --> 40:28.904
equipment
from the original project...

40:28.948 --> 40:30.776
[computer chiming]

40:30.819 --> 40:34.257
Including his old hand link
for Ziggy.

40:34.301 --> 40:35.955
♪

40:35.998 --> 40:39.437
- What is it?

40:39.480 --> 40:40.568
- It's bad.

40:40.612 --> 40:43.745
[rhythmic chiming]

40:43.789 --> 40:50.709
♪

41:01.502 --> 41:04.810
[Human League's
"Don't You Want Me"]

41:04.853 --> 41:10.163
♪

41:10.206 --> 41:12.600
- Buy you a drink?

41:12.644 --> 41:15.342
- No, thanks,
I've already got one.

41:15.385 --> 41:17.344
- You wanna get out of here?

41:17.387 --> 41:19.302
My place is right down
the street.

41:19.346 --> 41:22.480
- That's an interesting offer,

41:22.523 --> 41:24.786
but I'm actually
meeting someone hopefully soon.

41:24.830 --> 41:27.833
- [laughs]
All right, you wanna dance?

41:27.876 --> 41:29.878
- ♪ Don't you want me, baby?

41:29.922 --> 41:32.533
- Come on, I'm a
really good dancer.

41:32.577 --> 41:34.317
You know what they say
about good dancers.

41:34.361 --> 41:36.015
- ♪ Oh
